The paper deals with distributed algorithms for subgraph detection, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC). The problem involves communication networks, so it is also related to network protocols and architectures (cs.NI). The paper discusses upper and lower bounds for the problem, which is a common theme in distributed algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves limited bandwidth, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI, cs.IT). Overall, these categories seem to be the most relevant for this paper.
